Author: Fatih Naz <86602083+fatiihnaz@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Sat May 30 23:41:02 2026 +0300

    perf: move CMS draft/cache state into an external store to cut re-renders
    
    React context has no per-field subscription, so keeping the collection caches and live-edit draft overlays in the context value re-rendered every CollectionItem/CollectionRegion/EditableRegion on the page on every keystroke. They now live in a tiny zero-dependency store (lib/store.js); consumers subscribe to narrow slices via useStoreSelector, so typing in one row/region only re-renders the consumers that read it. The provider no longer re-renders on draft writes, and the content autosave effect is driven by a store subscription instead of a [drafts] effect dependency.
    
    Also fixes two collection cache bugs: a failed (re)fetch no longer blanks already-rendered content (the error path preserves the prior items/item instead of writing []/null), and a list refetch no longer clobbers a row being edited (the item-cache seeding pass skips slugs with a live local draft).
    
    Internal context shape only: collectionItemCache/collectionListCache/collectionDrafts/drafts on the context value are replaced by collectionStore + contentDraftsStore. Public exports (useCollection, useCollectionItem, EditableRegion, CmsProvider props) are unchanged.
    
